<paragraph blockId="4.[151,526,1399,1463]" box="[151,393,1436,1463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,302,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Figs 5, 9–10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[314,344,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,452,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[151,1435,452,1439]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Lefroyothrips species—metascutum. (11) fasciatus holotype; (12) fasciatus paratype male; (13) fasciatus male; (14) lefroyi; (15) tribulationi; (16) varatharajani." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[356,385,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,453,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[152,1436,453,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–23. Lefroyothrips species. Female tergites VII–X, 17–19: (17) lefroyi; (18) pictus; (19) tribulationi. male tergite IX, 20–21: (20) pictus; (21) fasciatus. (22) lefroyi female sternites VI–VII. (23) fasciatus fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543161/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">19</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1508,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis box="[151,373,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Colour mainly yellow with light brown areas as follows: behind each compound eye, on pronotum longitudinally and sublaterally, on metascutum laterally, on tergites III–VII medially and with paired lateral areas; major setae dark brown; legs yellow; fore wings very weakly shaded, with slightly darker area at veinal fork; antennal segments brown to dark brown, III with constricted apex sharply paler and base also paler (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1360,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). With the character states of the generic diagnosis. Head without sculpture in ocellar region, transversely irregularly striate on posterior area, postocular ridge weakly developed (
<figureCitation box="[766,835,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); ocellar setae III arise within ocellar triangle, length about equal to distance between posterior ocelli, ocellar setae pair I irregularly placed. Antennal segments III and IV with constricted elongate apex. Pronotum with weak irregular transverse striae, inner pair of posteroangular setae slightly shorter than outer pair (
<figureCitation box="[571,654,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Metanotum weakly reticulate, median major setae arise well behind anterior margin, medially with 1 or 2 extra setae (
<figureCitation box="[708,791,1832,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,452,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[151,1435,452,1439]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Lefroyothrips species—metascutum. (11) fasciatus holotype; (12) fasciatus paratype male; (13) fasciatus male; (14) lefroyi; (15) tribulationi; (16) varatharajani." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); CPS near posterior of sclerite. Fore wing first vein with 2 setae distally. Tergites without sculpture lines medially. Sternite VII setal pair S2 arise well in front of margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1508,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1904,1930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">Measurements</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[391,491,1904,1930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="571">holotype</typeStatus>
in microns). Body length 1750. Head, length 110; width 169; ocellar setae III 25. Pronotum, length 140; width 210; posteroangular setae—inner 45, outer 50. Metascutum major setae 40. Fore wing length 850. Antennal segments III–VIII length 75, 75, 50, 60, 12, 15.
</paragraph>
