<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,294,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3041473308" collectionCode="III, IV" pageId="5" pageNumber="572" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
The antennae of this species are unusual among species of this genus, both for their dark colour and for the constricted elongate apex to segments 
<collectionCode box="[714,742,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">III</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[798,828,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">IV</collectionCode>
. The distribution of the dark areas on the yellow body is probably distinctive, as are the almost uniformly coloured fore wings. The metascutum of the 
<typeStatus box="[1243,1341,366,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">holotype</typeStatus>
has two extra setae medially, whereas both 
<typeStatus box="[543,650,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">paratypes</typeStatus>
have only one such median seta
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
